{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"I read poetry all the time"},{"time":3462,"text":"and write about it frequently"},{"time":5022,"text":"and take poems apart"},{"time":6630,"text":"to see how they work"},{"time":8273,"text":"because I'm a word person."},{"time":9980,"text":"I understand the world best, most fully,"},{"time":12757,"text":"in words rather than, say, pictures or numbers,"},{"time":15650,"text":"and when I have a new experience or a new feeling,"},{"time":18218,"text":"I'm a little frustrated"},{"time":19368,"text":"until I can try to put it into words."},{"time":22563,"text":"I think I've always been that way."},{"time":24874,"text":"I devoured science fiction as a child. I still do."},{"time":27720,"text":"And I found poems by Andrew Marvell"},{"time":30000,"text":"and Matthew Arnold and Emily Dickinson"},{"time":31718,"text":"and William Butler Yeats"},{"time":33122,"text":"because they were quoted in science fiction,"},{"time":35402,"text":"and I loved their sounds"},{"time":36563,"text":"and I went on to read about ottava rima"},{"time":39970,"text":"and medial caesuras and enjambment"},{"time":42979,"text":"and all that other technical stuff"},{"time":44810,"text":"that you care about if you already care about poems,"},{"time":48930,"text":"because poems already made me happier"},{"time":52176,"text":"and sadder and more alive."},{"time":54259,"text":"And I became a poetry critic"},{"time":56088,"text":"because I wanted to know how and why."}]},{"cues":[{"time":60828,"text":"Now, poetry isn't one thing that serves one purpose"},{"time":65620,"text":"any more than music or computer programming"},{"time":68724,"text":"serve one purpose."},{"time":70586,"text":"The greek word poem, it just means \"a made thing,\""},{"time":74554,"text":"and poetry is a set of techniques,"},{"time":76567,"text":"ways of making patterns"},{"time":78518,"text":"that put emotions into words."},{"time":80607,"text":"The more techniques you know,"},{"time":82617,"text":"the more things you can make,"},{"time":85069,"text":"and the more patterns you can recognize"},{"time":88289,"text":"in things you might already like or love."}]},{"cues":[{"time":92454,"text":"That said, poetry does seem to be"},{"time":95491,"text":"especially good at certain things."},{"time":98425,"text":"For example, we are all going to die."},{"time":104930,"text":"Poetry can help us live with that."},{"time":107653,"text":"Poems are made of words, nothing but words."},{"time":110226,"text":"The particulars in poems are like"},{"time":112618,"text":"the particularities, the personalities,"},{"time":114114,"text":"that distinguish people from one another."},{"time":117391,"text":"Poems are easy to share, easy to pass on,"},{"time":120162,"text":"and when you read a poem, you can imagine"},{"time":121982,"text":"someone's speaking to you or for you,"},{"time":125990,"text":"maybe even someone far away"},{"time":127905,"text":"or someone made up or someone deceased."},{"time":132337,"text":"That's why we can go to poems when we want to"},{"time":136782,"text":"remember something or someone,"},{"time":139220,"text":"to celebrate or to look beyond death"},{"time":142332,"text":"or to say goodbye,"},{"time":144192,"text":"and that's one reason poems can seem important,"},{"time":148012,"text":"even to people who aren't me,"},{"time":150035,"text":"who don't so much live in a world of words."},{"time":154740,"text":"The poet Frank O'Hara said,"},{"time":156836,"text":"\"If you don't need poetry, bully for you,\""},{"time":160090,"text":"but he also said when he didn't\nwant to be alive anymore,"},{"time":163722,"text":"the thought that he wouldn't write any more poems"},{"time":166232,"text":"had stopped him."},{"time":168100,"text":"Poetry helps me want to be alive,"},{"time":170137,"text":"and I want to show you why by showing you how,"},{"time":173256,"text":"how a couple of poems react to the fact that"},{"time":176334,"text":"we're alive in one place at one time in one culture,"},{"time":179270,"text":"and in another we won't be alive at all."}]},{"cues":[{"time":184646,"text":"So here's one of the first poems I memorized."},{"time":188710,"text":"It could address a child or an adult."}]},{"cues":[{"time":193200,"text":"\"From far, from eve and morning"}]},{"cues":[{"time":196551,"text":"From yon twelve-winded sky,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":199377,"text":"The stuff of life to knit me"}]},{"cues":[{"time":201477,"text":"Blew hither; here am I."}]},{"cues":[{"time":203647,"text":"Now — for a breath I tarry"}]},{"cues":[{"time":205913,"text":"Nor yet disperse apart —"}]},{"cues":[{"time":208033,"text":"Take my hand quick and tell me,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":210109,"text":"What have you in your heart."}]},{"cues":[{"time":212212,"text":"Speak now, and I will answer;"}]},{"cues":[{"time":214669,"text":"How shall I help you, say;"}]},{"cues":[{"time":217249,"text":"Ere to the wind's twelve quarters"}]},{"cues":[{"time":219413,"text":"I take my endless way.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":222508,"text":"[A. E. Housman]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":224677,"text":"Now, this poem has appealed"},{"time":226121,"text":"to science fiction writers."},{"time":227524,"text":"It's furnished at least three science fiction titles,"},{"time":230693,"text":"I think because it says poems can brings us news"},{"time":233421,"text":"from the future or the past"},{"time":235414,"text":"or across the world,"},{"time":238221,"text":"because their patterns can seem to tell you"},{"time":240926,"text":"what's in somebody's heart."},{"time":242677,"text":"It says poems can bring people together temporarily,"},{"time":245549,"text":"which I think is true,"},{"time":247629,"text":"and it sticks in my head not just because it rhymes"},{"time":251166,"text":"but for how it rhymes,"},{"time":252604,"text":"cleanly and simply on the two and four,"},{"time":254991,"text":"\"say\" and \"way,\""},{"time":256228,"text":"with anticipatory hints on the one and three,"},{"time":259035,"text":"\"answer\" and \"quarters,\""},{"time":260660,"text":"as if the poem itself were coming together."},{"time":264535,"text":"It plays up the fact that we die"},{"time":266547,"text":"by exaggerating the speed of our lives."},{"time":268850,"text":"A few years on Earth become"},{"time":271128,"text":"one speech, one breath."},{"time":273367,"text":"It's a poem about loneliness --"},{"time":275526,"text":"the \"I\" in the poem feels no connection will last —"},{"time":278629,"text":"and it might look like a plea for help"},{"time":280541,"text":"'til you get to the word \"help,\""},{"time":283051,"text":"where this \"I\" facing you, taking your hand,"},{"time":285593,"text":"is more like a teacher or a genie,"},{"time":287574,"text":"or at least that's what he wants to believe."},{"time":290298,"text":"It would not be the first time a poet had"},{"time":293413,"text":"written the poem that he wanted to hear."}]},{"cues":[{"time":298275,"text":"Now, this next poem really changed"},{"time":301018,"text":"what I liked and what I read"},{"time":303014,"text":"and what I felt I could read as an adult."},{"time":305373,"text":"It might not make any sense to you"},{"time":307012,"text":"if you haven't seen it before."}]},{"cues":[{"time":310942,"text":"\"The Garden\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":313150,"text":"\"Oleander: coral"}]},{"cues":[{"time":315541,"text":"from lipstick ads in the 50's."}]},{"cues":[{"time":318101,"text":"Fruit of the tree of such knowledge"}]},{"cues":[{"time":321069,"text":"To smack\n(thin air)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":323013,"text":"meaning kiss or hit."}]},{"cues":[{"time":325111,"text":"It appears"}]},{"cues":[{"time":326230,"text":"in the guise of outworn usages"}]},{"cues":[{"time":328249,"text":"because we are bad?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":331120,"text":"Big masculine threat,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":332957,"text":"insinuating and slangy.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":335507,"text":"[Rae Armantrout]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":337705,"text":"Now, I found this poem in an anthology"},{"time":340453,"text":"of almost equally confusing poems in 1989."},{"time":343275,"text":"I just heard that there were these scandalous writers"},{"time":345293,"text":"called Language poets who didn't make any sense,"},{"time":347920,"text":"and I wanted to go and see\nfor myself what they were like,"},{"time":350188,"text":"and some of them didn't do much for me,"},{"time":351878,"text":"but this writer, Rae Armantrout,"},{"time":353430,"text":"did an awful lot, and I kept reading her"},{"time":356037,"text":"until I felt I knew what was going on,"},{"time":359228,"text":"as I do with this poem."}]},{"cues":[{"time":360493,"text":"It's about the Garden of Eden and the Fall"},{"time":363614,"text":"and the Biblical story of the Fall,"},{"time":367170,"text":"in which sex as we know it"},{"time":369322,"text":"and death and guilt"},{"time":370600,"text":"come into the world at the same time."},{"time":372609,"text":"It's also about how appearances deceive,"},{"time":374818,"text":"how our culture can sweep us along"},{"time":377242,"text":"into doing and saying things we didn't intend"},{"time":379610,"text":"or don't like, and Armantrout's style"},{"time":382080,"text":"is trying to help us stop or slow down."},{"time":385518,"text":"\"Smack\" can mean \"kiss\" as in air kisses,"},{"time":389952,"text":"as in lip-smacking,"},{"time":390917,"text":"but that can lead to \"smack\" as in \"hit\""},{"time":393279,"text":"as in domestic abuse,"},{"time":395394,"text":"because sexual attraction can seem threatening."},{"time":399202,"text":"The red that means fertility"},{"time":401468,"text":"can also mean poison."},{"time":403170,"text":"Oleander is poisonous."},{"time":404263,"text":"And outworn usages like \"smack\" for \"kiss\""},{"time":407950,"text":"or \"hit\" can help us see"},{"time":410607,"text":"how our unacknowledged assumptions"},{"time":412925,"text":"can make us believe we are bad,"},{"time":414920,"text":"either because sex is sinful"},{"time":416962,"text":"or because we tolerate so much sexism."},{"time":419802,"text":"We let guys tell women what to do."},{"time":422898,"text":"The poem reacts to old lipstick ads,"},{"time":425511,"text":"and its edginess about statement,"},{"time":427572,"text":"its reversals and halts, have everything to do"},{"time":429894,"text":"with resisting the language of ads"},{"time":432115,"text":"that want to tell us so easily what to want,"},{"time":435323,"text":"what to do, what to think."},{"time":436723,"text":"That resistance is a lot of the point of the poem,"},{"time":439267,"text":"which shows me, Armantrout shows me"},{"time":441435,"text":"what it's like to hear grave threats"},{"time":443401,"text":"and mortal dishonesty in the language"},{"time":445949,"text":"of everyday life, and once she's done that,"},{"time":448516,"text":"I think she can show other people, women and men,"},{"time":452976,"text":"what it's like to feel that way"},{"time":454451,"text":"and say to other people, women and men"},{"time":457157,"text":"who feel so alienated or so threatened"},{"time":460070,"text":"that they're not alone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":462011,"text":"Now, how do I know that I'm right"},{"time":465479,"text":"about this somewhat confusing poem?"},{"time":467457,"text":"Well in this case, I emailed\nthe poet a draft of my talk"},{"time":470198,"text":"and she said, \"Yeah, yeah, that's about it.\""},{"time":473034,"text":"Yeah. (Laughter) (Applause)"},{"time":476949,"text":"But usually, you can't know. You never know."},{"time":479875,"text":"You can't be sure, and that's okay."},{"time":482429,"text":"All we can do we is listen to poems"},{"time":484030,"text":"and look at poems and guess"},{"time":485689,"text":"and see if they can bring us what we need,"},{"time":488171,"text":"and if you're wrong about some part of a poem,"},{"time":491140,"text":"nothing bad will happen."},{"time":495071,"text":"Now, this next poem is older than Armantrout's,"},{"time":497854,"text":"but a little younger than A. E. Housman's."}]},{"cues":[{"time":501618,"text":"\"The Brave Man\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":503486,"text":"\"The sun, that brave man,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":506170,"text":"Comes through boughs that lie in wait,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":508890,"text":"That brave man."}]},{"cues":[{"time":511315,"text":"Green and gloomy eyes"}]},{"cues":[{"time":512900,"text":"In dark forms of the grass"}]},{"cues":[{"time":514728,"text":"Run away."}]},{"cues":[{"time":516245,"text":"The good stars,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":517970,"text":"Pale helms and spiky spurs,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":520657,"text":"Run away."}]},{"cues":[{"time":522047,"text":"Fears of my bed,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":523402,"text":"Fears of life and fears of death,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":525880,"text":"Run away."}]},{"cues":[{"time":527360,"text":"That brave man comes up"}]},{"cues":[{"time":529656,"text":"From below and walks without meditation,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":532576,"text":"That brave man.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":534353,"text":"[Wallace Stevens]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":537343,"text":"Now, the sun in this poem,"},{"time":539696,"text":"in Wallace Stevens' poem, seems so grave"},{"time":542185,"text":"because the person in the poem is so afraid."},{"time":545656,"text":"The sun comes up in the morning through branches,"},{"time":548143,"text":"dispels the dew, the eyes, on the grass,"},{"time":551082,"text":"and defeats stars envisioned as armies."},{"time":554487,"text":"\"Brave\" has its old sense of showy"},{"time":556456,"text":"as well as its modern sense, courage."},{"time":558700,"text":"This sun is not afraid to show his face."},{"time":562040,"text":"But the person in the poem is afraid."},{"time":565392,"text":"He might have been up all night."},{"time":566931,"text":"That is the reveal Stevens\nsaves for that fourth stanza,"},{"time":570913,"text":"where run away has become a refrain."},{"time":573691,"text":"This person might want to run away too,"},{"time":575883,"text":"but fortified by the sun's example,"},{"time":578173,"text":"he might just rise."},{"time":580898,"text":"Stevens saves that sonically odd word \"meditation\""},{"time":585176,"text":"for the end."},{"time":586850,"text":"Unlike the sun, human beings think."},{"time":589751,"text":"We meditate on past and future, life and death,"},{"time":593848,"text":"above and below."},{"time":596394,"text":"And it can make us afraid."}]},{"cues":[{"time":600178,"text":"Poems, the patterns in poems,"},{"time":602248,"text":"show us not just what somebody thought"},{"time":604190,"text":"or what someone did or what happened"},{"time":605862,"text":"but what it was like to be a person like that,"},{"time":610658,"text":"to be so anxious, so lonely, so inquisitive,"},{"time":614348,"text":"so goofy, so preposterous, so brave."},{"time":620234,"text":"That's why poems can seem at once so durable,"},{"time":623880,"text":"so personal, and so ephemeral,"},{"time":625921,"text":"like something inside and outside you at once."},{"time":629048,"text":"The Scottish poet Denise Riley compares poetry"},{"time":632383,"text":"to a needle, a sliver of outside I cradle inside,"},{"time":636501,"text":"and the American poet Terrance Hayes"},{"time":638909,"text":"wrote six poems called \"Wind in a Box.\""},{"time":641992,"text":"One of them asks, \"Tell me,"},{"time":643428,"text":"what am I going to do when I'm dead?\""},{"time":646062,"text":"And the answer is that he'll stay with us"},{"time":648792,"text":"or won't stay with us inside us as wind,"},{"time":651668,"text":"as air, as words."}]},{"cues":[{"time":654890,"text":"It is easier than ever to find poems"},{"time":657548,"text":"that might stay inside you, that might stay with you,"},{"time":661140,"text":"from long, long ago, or from right this minute,"},{"time":663598,"text":"from far away or from right close to where you live,"},{"time":666172,"text":"almost no matter where you live."},{"time":669498,"text":"Poems can help you say, help\nyou show how you're feeling,"},{"time":672967,"text":"but they can also introduce you"},{"time":675407,"text":"to feelings, ways of being in the world,"},{"time":677690,"text":"people, very much unlike you,"},{"time":680067,"text":"maybe even people from long, long ago."},{"time":684648,"text":"Some poems even tell you"},{"time":686735,"text":"that that is what they can do."},{"time":691286,"text":"That's what John Keats is doing"},{"time":693956,"text":"in his most mysterious, perhaps, poem."},{"time":698324,"text":"It's mysterious because it's probably unfinished,"},{"time":702236,"text":"he probably left it unfinished,"},{"time":704565,"text":"and because it might be meant"},{"time":706162,"text":"for a character in a play,"},{"time":708788,"text":"but it might just be Keats' thinking"},{"time":710465,"text":"about what his own writing,"},{"time":712100,"text":"his handwriting, could do,"},{"time":714300,"text":"and in it I hear, at least I hear, mortality,"},{"time":718190,"text":"and I hear the power of older poetic techniques,"},{"time":721719,"text":"and I have the feeling, you might have the feeling,"},{"time":724250,"text":"of meeting even for an instant, almost becoming,"},{"time":727236,"text":"someone else from long ago,"},{"time":728758,"text":"someone quite memorable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":731473,"text":"\"This living hand, now warm and capable"}]},{"cues":[{"time":734649,"text":"Of earnest grasping, would, if it were cold"}]},{"cues":[{"time":738359,"text":"And in the icy silence of the tomb,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":740750,"text":"So haunt thy days and chill thy dreaming nights"}]},{"cues":[{"time":744326,"text":"That thou would wish thine own heart dry of blood\n"}]},{"cues":[{"time":748260,"text":"So in my veins red life might stream again,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":751911,"text":"And thou be conscience-calm’d -- see here it is --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":756810,"text":"I hold it towards you.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":761110,"text":"Thanks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":763417,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}